No. She worked at a temp agency,
so she just had jobs here and there.

144
00:12:36,054 --> 00:12:38,579
She must have had someone
that she forgot to list.

145
00:12:38,656 --> 00:12:41,853
Try her high school.
Everyone has friends from high school.

146
00:12:41,926 --> 00:12:43,450
No, they don't.

147
00:12:43,528 --> 00:12:46,395
Maybe they have people they talk to,
or do things with...

148
00:12:46,464 --> 00:12:48,398
but they're not really friends.

149
00:12:48,466 --> 00:12:50,229
They're just filler.

150
00:12:52,570 --> 00:12:54,162
What? It's true.

151
00:12:55,373 --> 00:12:57,273
I want a glass of wine.

152
00:12:57,509 --> 00:12:58,737
Oh, God.

153
00:12:59,144 --> 00:13:00,634
It's so weird.

154
00:13:01,646 --> 00:13:03,876
Who the hell was Emily Previn?

155
00:13:06,251 --> 00:13:07,843
Nate, are you okay?

156
00:13:08,620 --> 00:13:11,953
- Yeah, I'm fine.
- 'Cause your eyes look really weird.

157
00:13:12,323 --> 00:13:16,953
Yeah, it's just this medication I'm taking.
It makes me a little drowsy. That's all.

158
00:13:17,996 --> 00:13:19,258
Honestly.

159
00:13:23,701 --> 00:13:26,033
Maybe Emily Previn was autistic.

160
00:13:26,104 --> 00:13:30,973
I read an article about a high-functioning
autistic person who didn't need people.

161
00:13:31,042 --> 00:13:34,341
She just had a job
designing these big cattle slaughterhouses.

162
00:13:34,412 --> 00:13:37,040
At night, she came home
and sat in a machine...

163
00:13:37,115 --> 00:13:39,310
