like she was being hugged.

164
00:13:39,384 --> 00:13:41,909
And that was all the intimacy she needed.

165
00:13:41,986 --> 00:13:43,613
That's really upsetting.

166
00:13:43,688 --> 00:13:46,350
I don't see why
this person has to be mentally ill...

167
00:13:46,424 --> 00:13:50,884
just because she had a life that doesn't
conform to a familiar image in our heads.

168
00:13:51,162 --> 00:13:53,824
Maybe she was living the life she wanted.

169
00:13:53,898 --> 00:13:56,093
A life without the hassle of other people.

170
00:13:56,167 --> 00:13:58,294
What kind of a life is that?

171
00:14:03,141 --> 00:14:04,802
"Well, I'm sorry, Your Honor...

172
00:14:04,876 --> 00:14:08,039
"but how was I supposed to know
it was your car?"

173
00:14:09,214 --> 00:14:12,672
- I don't think I could be a public defender.
- No? Why not?

174
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:15,844
